---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About | Shayan Rabbi"
  description="About Shayan Rabbi and the intent behind the website."
>
  <section class="page-grid">
    <article class="surface">
      <div class="article">
        <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
        <h1 class="page-title">From heart surgery to venture, now building in public.</h1>
        <p>
          I am Shayan Rabbi, based in Toronto. My public GitHub bio says it
          plainly: I used to do heart surgery; now I do venture.
        </p>
        <p>
          This website is where that transition becomes legible. It is meant to
          hold projects, essays, design investigations, and the infrastructure
          work that sits underneath them.
        </p>
        <p>
          The through-line is not a single job title. It is an interest in
          systems, judgment, and how to build things that are both useful and
          intellectually honest.
        </p>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="surface">
      <div class="article">
        <p class="eyebrow">What this site is for</p>
        <ul>
          <li>A public record of projects and experiments</li>
          <li>A place to write longer ideas without collapsing them into social fragments</li>
          <li>A home for design thinking about what the web should do, not just how it should look</li>
          <li>A system that can keep evolving as the work evolves</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </article>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
